# 1. Executive Summary

The AI Customer Support Automation System is designed to automate repetitive customer interactions while improving response quality, reducing operational costs, and providing continuous customer assistance.

The proposed solution follows a modular multi-agent architecture where specialized AI agents handle different categories of customer requests, including general support, order management, and product recommendations.

The system combines FastAPI for backend services, CrewAI for agent orchestration, Groq as the primary cloud-based Large Language Model (LLM), and Ollama as a local fallback model. This hybrid approach provides high availability, improved reliability, and flexibility while maintaining a low infrastructure cost.

The architecture is designed to support future enterprise-scale deployments through modular components and horizontal scalability.



# 2. Business Requirements

Modern eCommerce businesses require intelligent customer support systems capable of handling a large volume of customer interactions without increasing operational costs.

The proposed solution addresses the following business requirements:

